cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the development of algorithms for predicting Estimated Times of Arrival (ETA) in public transport networks using Automatic Vehicle Location (AVL) data. This involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and statistical analysis (cs.LG) of the data. The paper also discusses the use of information technology (cs.IT) in collecting and processing the data. Additionally, the paper highlights the need for standardization and quality control in the development and reporting of these algorithms, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
